---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Buying Guide', url: '/buying-guide' },
  { name: 'Property tax guide', url: '/buying-guide/property-tax-guide' },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Property Tax Guide (What, Why, How to Pay) | PropDiscover"
  description="Property tax guide for homeowners: what it is, who pays it, what affects it, documents to keep, and how to avoid penalties."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  jsonLd={{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": breadcrumbs.map((b, i) => ({
      "@type": "ListItem",
      "position": i + 1,
      "name": b.name,
      "item": `https://propdiscover.com${b.url}`,
    })),
  }}
>
  <section class="py-14 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Property tax guide</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">
        Property tax is typically paid to your local municipal body. Keeping payments current helps avoid penalties and makes resale smoother.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 p-6 md:p-8 space-y-7 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Who pays property tax?</h2>
          <p>Usually, the owner of the property is responsible. In some rental arrangements, tenants may pay it contractually, but ownership liability remains important.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What affects the tax amount</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>Location (zone/ward), property usage (residential/commercial).</li>
            <li>Built-up area / carpet area and construction type.</li>
            <li>Municipal valuation method and rebates/penalties.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What to keep for records</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>Latest paid receipts and challans.</li>
            <li>Mutation/khata details (where applicable).</li>
            <li>Sale deed and basic property identifiers (door no./plot no.).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="pt-2">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Next reads</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li><a class="text-primary-700 hover:text-primary-800" href="/buying-guide/stamp-duty-guide">Stamp duty & registration guide</a></li>
            <li><a class="text-primary-700 hover:text-primary-800" href="/buying-guide/how-to-buy-property">How to buy property</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

